HEADWORD: Gutturize
<hw>Gut"tur*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>guttur</ets> throat.]</ety> <def>To make in the throat; to
gutturalize.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For which the Germans <ex>gutturize</ex> a sound.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gutturo-</ent>⟦br⟧
